			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>How do submarines affect this? They do seem to be primarily &#8220;defensive&#8221; naval weapons exploiting the ocean depths, in the sense that attack submarines are all about area denial in the water (although the Taiwan Strait is so shallow that it seems questionable that any submarine could hide in there for long).</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

		</article><!-- .comment-body -->

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='https://scholars-stage.org/fear-the-logic-of-the-first-strike/?replytocom=2467#respond' data-commentid="2467" data-postid="2318" data-belowelement="div-comment-2467" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Brett" aria-label='Reply to Brett'>Reply</a></div>		</div><!-- #comment-## -->
		<div id="comment-2468" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 parent">
		<article id="div-comment-2468" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
					<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/8f8ff21a67437febebc70afd19364e95?s=32&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/8f8ff21a67437febebc70afd19364e95?s=64&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-32 photo' height='32' width='32' loading='lazy'/><b class="fn">Antipodean Coward</b>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

